    "### Short-Form vs Feed-Based: Formal Group Comparison (Dataset #1)\n",
    "\n",
    "We collapse the five platforms into two groups and run Welch's t-tests to formally test whether short-form users (TikTok, Instagram, Snapchat) differ from feed-based users (Facebook, YouTube) on all key outcomes. Welch's t-test is appropriate here because the two groups have very different sample sizes (n≈416 vs n≈133)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "75d81445",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sf = df1[df1['Platform_Type'] == 'Short-Form']\n",
    "fb = df1[df1['Platform_Type'] == 'Feed-Based']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Short-Form n={len(sf)} | Feed-Based n={len(fb)}\\n\")\n",
    "print(f\"{'Outcome':<45} {'Short-Form':>12} {'Feed-Based':>12} {'t':>8} {'p':>10} {'sig':>5}\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 95)\n",
    "\n",
    "outcomes = {\n",
    "    'Avg Daily Usage (hours)':     'Avg_Daily_Usage_Hours',\n",
    "    'Addiction Score (1-9)':       'Addicted_Score',\n",
    "    'Mental Health Score (1-10)':  'Mental_Health_Score',\n",
    "    'Sleep Hours per Night':       'Sleep_Hours_Per_Night',\n",
    "    'Academic Impact (0/1)':       'acad_impact_bin',\n",
